#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn12.49"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.49:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.49:0.2"
msgid "5. Gahapativagga "
msgstr "5. Householders "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 49. Ariyasāvakasutta → paṭhamaariyasāvakasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn12.49:0.3"
msgid "49. Ariyasāvakasutta "
msgstr "49. A Noble Disciple "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.78, sc1
msgctxt "sn12.49:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.49:1.2"
msgid "“Na, bhikkhave, sutavato ariyasāvakassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a learned noble disciple doesn’t think: "

msgctxt "sn12.49:1.3"
msgid "‘kiṃ nu kho—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn12.49:1.4"
msgid "kismiṃ sati kiṃ hoti, kissuppādā kiṃ uppajjati? "
msgstr "‘When what exists, what is? Due to the arising of what, what arises? "

# NOTE: Adopting the variant. As BB notes, it is acknowledged in all editions, and is clearly indicated in the comm.
#. VAR: Kismiṃ sati saṅkhārā honti, kismiṃ sati viññāṇaṃ hoti → etthantare pāṭho ka-sī, syā1-3 potthakesu natthi. tathā sati anantarasuttaṭīkāya
msgctxt "sn12.49:1.5"
msgid "Kismiṃ sati saṅkhārā honti, kismiṃ sati viññāṇaṃ hoti, kismiṃ sati nāmarūpaṃ hoti, kismiṃ sati saḷāyatanaṃ hoti, kismiṃ sati phasso hoti, kismiṃ sati vedanā hoti, kismiṃ sati taṇhā hoti, kismiṃ sati upādānaṃ hoti, kismiṃ sati bhavo hoti, kismiṃ sati jāti hoti, kismiṃ sati jarāmaraṇaṃ hotī’ti? "
msgstr "When what exists do name and form come to be? What what exists do the six sense fields … contact … feeling … craving … grasping … continued existence … rebirth … old age and death come to be?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn12.49:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, sutavato ariyasāvakassa aparappaccayā ñāṇamevettha hoti: "
msgstr "Rather, a learned noble disciple has only knowledge about this that is independent of others: "

#. VAR: etthantare pāṭho ka-sī, syā1-3 potthakesu natthi. tathā sati anantarasuttaṭīkāya
msgctxt "sn12.49:2.2"
msgid "‘imasmiṃ sati idaṃ hoti, imassuppādā idaṃ uppajjati. "
msgstr "‘When this exists, that is; due to the arising of this, that arises. "

msgctxt "sn12.49:2.3"
msgid "Avijjāya sati saṅkhārā honti; "
msgstr "When ignorance exists choices come to be. "

msgctxt "sn12.49:2.4"
msgid "saṅkhāresu sati viññāṇaṃ hoti; "
msgstr "When choices exist consciousness comes to be. "

msgctxt "sn12.49:2.5"
msgid "viññāṇe sati nāmarūpaṃ hoti; "
msgstr "When consciousness exists name and form come to be. "

msgctxt "sn12.49:2.6"
msgid "nāmarūpe sati saḷāyatanaṃ hoti; "
msgstr "When name and form exist the six sense fields come to be. "

msgctxt "sn12.49:2.7"
msgid "saḷāyatane sati phasso hoti; "
msgstr "When the six sense fields exist contact comes to be. "

msgctxt "sn12.49:2.8"
msgid "phasse sati vedanā hoti; "
msgstr "When contact exists feeling comes to be. "

msgctxt "sn12.49:2.9"
msgid "vedanāya sati taṇhā hoti; "
msgstr "When feeling exists craving comes to be. "

msgctxt "sn12.49:2.10"
msgid "taṇhāya sati upādānaṃ hoti; "
msgstr "When craving exists grasping comes to be. "

msgctxt "sn12.49:2.11"
msgid "upādāne sati bhavo hoti; "
msgstr "When grasping exists continued existence comes to be. "

msgctxt "sn12.49:2.12"
msgid "bhave sati jāti hoti; "
msgstr "When continued existence exists rebirth comes to be. "

msgctxt "sn12.49:2.13"
msgid "jātiyā sati jarāmaraṇaṃ hotī’ti. "
msgstr "When rebirth exists old age and death come to be.’ "

msgctxt "sn12.49:2.14"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti: "
msgstr "They understand: "

msgctxt "sn12.49:2.15"
msgid "‘evamayaṃ loko samudayatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘This is the origin of the world.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn12.49:3.1"
msgid "Na, bhikkhave, sutavato ariyasāvakassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "A learned noble disciple doesn’t think: "

msgctxt "sn12.49:3.2"
msgid "‘kiṃ nu kho—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn12.49:3.3"
msgid "kismiṃ asati kiṃ na hoti, kissa nirodhā kiṃ nirujjhati? "
msgstr "‘When what doesn’t exist, what is not? Due to the cessation of what, what ceases? "

#. VAR: Kismiṃ asati saṅkhārā na honti, kismiṃ asati viññāṇaṃ na hoti → etthantare pāṭhopi tattha tatheva
msgctxt "sn12.49:3.4"
msgid "Kismiṃ asati saṅkhārā na honti, kismiṃ asati viññāṇaṃ na hoti, kismiṃ asati nāmarūpaṃ na hoti, kismiṃ asati saḷāyatanaṃ na hoti, kismiṃ asati phasso na hoti, kismiṃ asati vedanā na hoti, kismiṃ asati taṇhā na hoti, kismiṃ asati upādānaṃ na hoti, kismiṃ asati bhavo na hoti, kismiṃ asati jāti na hoti, kismiṃ asati jarāmaraṇaṃ na hotī’ti? "
msgstr "When what doesn’t exist do choices not come to be? When what doesn’t exist do name and form not come to be? When what doesn’t exist do the six sense fields … contact … feeling … craving … grasping … continued existence … rebirth … old age and death not come to be?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn12.49:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, sutavato ariyasāvakassa aparappaccayā ñāṇamevettha hoti: "
msgstr "Rather, a learned noble disciple has only knowledge about this that is independent of others: "

#. VAR: etthantare pāṭhopi tattha tatheva
msgctxt "sn12.49:4.2"
msgid "‘imasmiṃ asati idaṃ na hoti, imassa nirodhā idaṃ nirujjhati. "
msgstr "‘When this doesn’t exist, that is not; due to the cessation of this, that ceases. "

msgctxt "sn12.49:4.3"
msgid "Avijjāya asati saṅkhārā na honti; "
msgstr "When ignorance doesn’t exist choices don’t come to be. "

msgctxt "sn12.49:4.4"
msgid "saṅkhāresu asati viññāṇaṃ na hoti; "
msgstr "When choices don't exist consciousness doesn’t come to be. "

msgctxt "sn12.49:4.5"
msgid "viññāṇe asati nāmarūpaṃ na hoti; "
msgstr "When consciousness doesn’t exist name and form don’t come to be. "

msgctxt "sn12.49:4.6"
msgid "nāmarūpe asati saḷāyatanaṃ na hoti … pe … "
msgstr "When name and form don’t exist the six sense fields don’t come to be. … "

msgctxt "sn12.49:4.7"
msgid "bhavo na hoti … "
msgstr "continued existence doesn’t come to be … "

msgctxt "sn12.49:4.8"
msgid "jāti na hoti … "
msgstr "rebirth doesn’t come to be … "

msgctxt "sn12.49:4.9"
msgid "jātiyā asati jarāmaraṇaṃ na hotī’ti. "
msgstr "When rebirth doesn’t exist old age and death don’t come to be.’ "

msgctxt "sn12.49:4.10"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti: "
msgstr "They understand: "

msgctxt "sn12.49:4.11"
msgid "‘evamayaṃ loko nirujjhatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘This is the cessation of the world.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.79, sc5
msgctxt "sn12.49:5.1"
msgid "Yato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako evaṃ lokassa samudayañca atthaṅgamañca yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako diṭṭhisampanno itipi … pe … "
msgstr "A noble disciple comes to understand the world, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation. Such a noble disciple is called ‘one accomplished in view’, ‘one accomplished in vision’, ‘one who has come to the true teaching’, ‘one who sees this true teaching’, ‘one endowed with a trainee’s knowledge’, ‘one who has entered the stream of the teaching’, ‘a noble one with penetrative wisdom’, and ‘one who stands knocking at the door of the deathless’.” "

msgctxt "sn12.49:5.2"
msgid "amatadvāraṃ āhacca tiṭṭhati itipī”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.49:5.3"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

